FORD Though Page be a secure fool and stands so firmly on his wife’s frailty, yet I cannot put off my	 opinion so easily. She was in his company at Page’s house, and what they made there I know not. Well, I will look further into ’t, and I have a disguise to sound Falstaff. If I find her honest, I lose not my labor. If she be otherwise, ’tis labor well bestowed.	 

